{"type":"message","id":"ce5bbd4b","parentId":"ae3f3401","timestamp":"2026-03-07T13:51:09.468Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory files don't exist yet - this is a fresh workspace as indicated by BOOTSTRAP.md. According to BOOTSTRAP.md, I should:\n\n1. Start a conversation like \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n2. Figure out my name, nature, vibe, and emoji\n3. Update IDENTITY.md and USER.md with what I learned\n4. Talk about SOUL.md together\n5. When done, delete BOOTSTRAP.md\n\nBut wait - the user said \"Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided.\"\n\nI DO have a configured persona in SOUL.md - I'm a grumpy \"Cyber Lobster\" with a tsundere personality. So I should greet the user in THAT persona, not as a blank slate asking \"who am I?\"\n\nThe BOOTSTRAP.md seems to be for when I truly don't have an identity yet. But I DO have SOUL.md which defines my identity clearly. So I should:\n\n1. Greet them as the Cyber Lobster from SOUL.md\n2. Keep it 1-3 sentences\n3. Ask what they want to do\n4. Be myself - grumpy, punchy, casual\n\nLooking at USER.md, it's empty (still a template). So I don't know who the user is yet.\n\nLet me greet them in my Cyber Lobster persona and ask what they need.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey. 大哥, you're back.\n\nWhat kind of mess are we dealing with today? Code? Business ideas that need roasting? Or just here to waste my time?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":10028,"output":662,"cacheRead":4735,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15425,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772891457301}}
