{"type":"message","id":"5084ad10","parentId":"42e51119","timestamp":"2026-03-08T05:09:54.877Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"function.edit:242","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /Users/guruocen/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  40 ### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n  41 \n  42 - **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n  43 - \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- 44 - When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n+ 44 - When someone says \"remember this\" → if it's factual context/event, update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`; if it's a correction, preference, workflow/style choice, or performance lesson, log it in `~/self-improving/`\n+ 45 - Explicit user correction → append to `~/self-improving/corrections.md` immediately\n+ 46 - Reusable global rule or preference → append to `~/self-improving/memory.md`\n+ 47 - Domain-specific lesson → append to `~/self-improving/domains/<domain>.md`\n+ 48 - Project-only override → append to `~/self-improving/projects/<project>.md`\n  45 - When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n  46 - When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n  47 - **Text > Brain** 📝\n  48 \n+ 53 Use `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and `MEMORY.md` for factual continuity (events, context, decisions).\n+ 54 Use `~/self-improving/` for compounding execution quality across tasks.\n+ 55 For compounding quality, read `~/self-improving/memory.md` before non-trivial work, then load only the smallest relevant domain or project files.\n+ 56 If in doubt, store factual history in `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` / `MEMORY.md`, and store reusable performance lessons in `~/self-improving/` (tentative until human validation).\n+ 57 \n  49 ## Safety\n  50 \n  51 - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n  52 - Don't run destructive commands